error: `result_fallback` requires `ttl` to be set (e.g. `ttl = 60`). It serves the last cached `Ok` value when a refresh returns `Err`, but a refresh only happens after an entry expires. Without a TTL entries never expire, so the function body is never re-run for a cached key and the fallback can never fire — making the option a no-op. Set a TTL so cached entries expire and `result_fallback` has something to fall back to.
